@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Our Teachers";
}

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div class="text-xs tracking-[3px] text-lumina-sage">THE HEART OF LUMINA</div>
        <h1 class="section-title text-6xl tracking-[-1.5px] mt-3">Our Teachers</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-lg mx-auto text-xl text-lumina-charcoal/80">Meet the guides who hold space for your practice with deep care, precision, and presence.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Thandi -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-x-12 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-5">
                <div class="aspect-[4/3] rounded-3xl overflow-hidden elegant-shadow">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494790108377-be9c29b29330?q=80&w=1200" class="w-full h-full object-cover" alt="Thandi Mokoena">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-7 mt-8 md:mt-0">
                <div class="uppercase tracking-[2px] text-xs text-lumina-sage">FOUNDER</div>
                <h2 class="text-5xl font-light tracking-tight mt-1">Thandi Mokoena</h2>
                <div class="text-lumina-terracotta mt-1">Reformer • Restorative • Prenatal</div>
                
                <div class="prose text-lumina-charcoal/80 mt-6">
                    <p>Thandi founded Lumina after her own journey from professional dance to physiotherapy to finding deep healing through mindful movement. She teaches with a rare combination of technical precision and profound compassion.</p>
                    <p>Her classes are known for their intelligent sequencing and the way she makes every person in the room feel truly seen.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-6 text-sm text-lumina-charcoal/60">
                    "Movement is medicine when it’s offered with presence."
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Liam -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-x-12 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-5 order-1 md:order-2">
                <div class="aspect-[4/3] rounded-3xl overflow-hidden elegant-shadow">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?q=80&w=1200" class="w-full h-full object-cover" alt="Liam van der Berg">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-7 mt-8 md:mt-0 order-2 md:order-1">
                <div class="uppercase tracking-[2px] text-xs text-lumina-sage">COACH</div>
                <h2 class="text-5xl font-light tracking-tight mt-1">Liam van der Berg</h2>
                <div class="text-lumina-terracotta mt-1">Mat Flow • Functional Movement • Strength</div>
                
                <div class="prose text-lumina-charcoal/80 mt-6">
                    <p>Liam brings a playful yet deeply grounded energy to every class. With a background in sports science and years working alongside physiotherapists, he has a gift for making complex movement simple and accessible.</p>
                    <p>He believes strength should feel good in the body, not punishing.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Aisha -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-x-12 items-center">
            <div class="md:col-span-5">
                <div class="aspect-[4/3] rounded-3xl overflow-hidden elegant-shadow">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1438761681033-6461ffad8d80?q=80&w=1200" class="w-full h-full object-cover" alt="Aisha Khan">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:col-span-7 mt-8 md:mt-0">
                <div class="uppercase tracking-[2px] text-xs text-lumina-sage">INCLUSIVE MOVEMENT SPECIALIST</div>
                <h2 class="text-5xl font-light tracking-tight mt-1">Aisha Khan</h2>
                <div class="text-lumina-terracotta mt-1">Adaptive Yoga • Chair Yoga • Low-Sensory</div>
                
                <div class="prose text-lumina-charcoal/80 mt-6">
                    <p>Aisha’s classes are sanctuaries. She has dedicated her practice to making movement truly accessible — for neurodivergent bodies, chronic illness, seniors, and anyone who has ever felt othered in traditional fitness spaces.</p>
                    <p>Her teaching is gentle, precise, and profoundly welcoming.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>